  "doc_id": "38830",
  "text": "We have identified at least three species of cecidomyiids in the cave, representing three genera in the tribe Cecidomyiidi. All of the species found in the cave are associated with the bat guano deposits, and specimens were obtained from Berlese samples of the two main guano deposits, the Lunch Spot and the Maternity Roost. Species of Bremia are usually associated with decaying materials, but probably more likely fill a predatory niche in the guano deposits (Gagné personal communication). There are records of Bremia sp. recorded from caves in Arkansas, Georgia, and Missouri [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). These records do not mention an ecological association.",
